   "source": [
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "4639fb24-e0fd-489d-bc3e-e3f90a280b45",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "[*********************100%***********************]  1 of 1 completed\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "ticker = 'AAPL'\n",
    "start_date = '2015-01-01'\n",
    "end_date = '2023-01-01'\n",
    "data = yf.download (ticker, start=start_date, end=end_date)\n",
    "data = data['Close']"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "263b4990-3eb6-431b-882b-d617e6cac6c3",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "returns = data.pct_change().dropna ()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "29c512ce-d4b4-49a9-a135-dd4aceb99551",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "mean_return = returns.mean()\n",
    "std_dev_return = returns.std()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "b0b0fae7-5453-4733-8ec3-26fdccf83ae8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def monte_carlo_simulation (start_price, days, mean_return, std_dev_return, num_simulations):\n",
    "    simulations= np.zeros((days, num_simulations))\n",
    "    simulations [0] = start_price\n",
    "    for t in range(1, days):\n",
    "        random_walk = np.random. normal (mean_return, std_dev_return, num_simulations)\n",
    "        simulations [t] = simulations [t - 1]*(1 + random_walk)\n",
    "    return simulations"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "de6ef5cb-6f16-4968-869a-7e9362845773",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "days= 252\n",
    "num_simulations = 100\n",
    "start_price = data.iloc[-1][\"AAPL\"]\n",
    "simulations = monte_carlo_simulation (start_price, days, mean_return, std_dev_return, num_simulations)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "e612825d-2447-406a-89ed-186b871f126c",
   "metadata": {
    "scrolled": true
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "colors = plt.cm.tab20 (np.arange(num_simulations) % 20)\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "for i in range (num_simulations):\n",
    "    plt.plot(simulations[:, i], color=colors [i], alpha=0.75, lw=1)\n",
    "plt.title(f'Monte Carlo Simulation for {ticker} Stock Price') \n",
    "plt.xlabel('Days')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Price') \n",
    "plt.ylabel('Stock Price')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,

      "Expected Price after 252 days: $169.96\n",

     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "end_prices = simulations [-1, :]\n",
    "std_dev_price = np. std (end_prices)\n",
    "expected_price = np.mean(end_prices)\n",
    "print (f\"Expected Price after {days} days: ${expected_price:.2f}\")\n",
    "print (f\"Standard Deviation of Price after {days} days: ${std_dev_price:.2f}\")"
   ]
  }
